metadata.description: A short unique identifer for the customer owning the resource. E.g. 'mc'='Marel Connect', 'io'='Innova'
The location of the data center the resorce will be deployed to.
Optional name extension. Useful when creating service specific resources within a group E.g. 'ingsvc', 'telenr'
The type of resource the name is being generated for. e.g. 'Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts'
Sometimes a 'kind' needs to be specified. Then this parameter needs to be provided. E.g. resource='Microsoft.Web/sites' kind='functionapp'
If name is for a repeated resource then this should be an integer >= 0
Determines if the name should include hyphens or not. e.g. 'mc-d-euw-data-kv' vs 'mcdeuwdatakv'
